            <h2>Iloilo City</h2>
            <h3>City of Love, My City, My Pride</h3>

            <img src="<?= $this->webroot ?>theme/weatherph/img/tourism/iloiloCity1.png" alt="">

            <p>The name Iloilo was derived from the Hiligaynon word Ilong- Ilong meaning ‘noselike’ that specifically referred to an islet in the Batiano River.
                Iloilio has an old city charm. It became a city in 1893 under the Spanish Law, then reverted to municipality status in 1898 under the American Regime and became a chartered city again in 1937. It was declared a Highly Urbanized City in 1981.</p>
            <p>The City is presently inhabited with an estimated half a million residents living in its six major districts - the City Proper, Jaro, Molo, Mandurriao, Arevalo, and La Paz. Among the City’s festivals, the grandest celebration ans the most famous is the Dinagyang, which falls every 4th Sunday of January. It is the celebration commemorating the arrival of the image of the Child Jesus as welcomed by the Aetas hundreds of years ago.</p>
            <p>In terms of tourism, Iloilo City is developing the culinary attractions of the six districts: La Paz Batchoy has already gained a national fame. Pancit Molo is also known around the country as a variant of a noodle soup; Jaro is proud of its delicacies like the biscocho, butterscotch, banana pinasugbo; Mandurriao would underscore the unique taste of its Cansi; Arevalo’s seafood is sumptuous with Tatoy’s and Breakthrough as the popular food trip destination; the City, of course is proud to promote grilled chicken. Foods take the stomach as a way to win the hearts and minds of those who come to visit Iloilo. Iloilo foods taste better because ultimately, Ilonggos are hospitable warm good-natured people</p>
            <p>The investment potentials of the city are in agribusiness: agri- based and aqua-based food processing; delicacies-making, furniture, gifts, toys and house wares and garments. In the area of trade and services: IT and IT enabled services, retail and wholesale trading, restaurants and eateries; in tourism-related investments; culinary attractions and themed tourism facilities and amenities. There is room for convention center, IT parks and buildings and housing subdivision projects.</p>
            <p>The City is also known for its competitiveness - high profitability of business, low labor cost, high growth of registered businesses, availability of good information technology training, presence of private and public sector organized training programs, good administration of justice, transparent local government, effective leadership of the local chief executive, and appropriate security environment for businesses.</p>

