            <h3>Iloilo City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Explore the City’s culture and heritage through a half- or one-day city tour. This includes the Museo Iloilo, Fort San Pedro, antique hunting, campus tours, and pasalubong shopping</li>
                <li>2. Visit La Paz district for a taste of authentic La Paz Batchoy or Molo district for the original Pancit Molo. Seafood cuisine is also famous in the Arevalo Beach area where one can dine by the shore</li>
                <li>3. Also in the Arevalo district, See how women weavers daintily operate Spanish era looms to make delicate jusi, piňa, and hablon fabrics of delicate designs. Buy finished products at Sinamay Dealer near Arevalo Plaza</li>
                <li>4. Capture the aura of the old Iloilo through its opulent churches like in Molo (St. Anne’s Parish) and Jaro (St. Elizabeth Metropolitan Cathedral)</li>
                <li>5. Participate in the City’s grand festivities like the Dinagyang Festival, Paraw Regatta Festival, which is the Asia’s oldest native boat sailing event, the Chinese New Year, and the Feast of our Lady of the Candles, which is the grandest religious festival in the Western Visayas.</li></ol>
            <h3>Profile</h3>
            <p>Official Name: City of Iloilo</p>
