            <p>By Sea: Ship – 18 hours.</p>
            <p>By Air: Airplane via Iloilo Airport – 50 minutes. From airport (Santa Barbara or Cabatuan) to Iloilo City: 20 minutes</p>

            <h3>Major cultural and tourism destinations</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Dinagyang Festival – every fourth Sunday of January</li>
                <li>2. Paraw Regatta Festival – every third weekend of February</li>
                <li>3. City Charter Anniversary Celebration – from 16th July to 25th August every year</li>
                <li>4. Iloilo Churches- St. Elizabeth Cathedral (Jaro) and St. Anne Church (Molo)</li>
            </ol>

